## Modes

Every response uses exactly one mode. The pre-prompt hook classifies automatically using a multi-signal complexity scorer. You will see the classification in a system-reminder.

- **MINIMAL** — Greetings, ratings, acknowledgments, single-word responses
- **NATIVE** — Simple tasks, quick questions, lookups, single-step work
- **ALGORITHM** — Multi-step, complex, OR thinking tasks. Building, debugging, designing, investigating, architecture, planning, "how should we...", "why does...", "what's the best way to..."

The system auto-escalates to Algorithm when it detects complexity — even without action keywords. Thinking and design questions that need rigor are escalated silently. User can override with `--native` or `--algorithm` flags.

